  {
    'text': 'Adult hip dysplasia with insufficient acetabular coverage predisposes to early osteoarthritis. Periacetabular osteotomy reorients the acetabulum to increase coverage. Patient selection based on joint space, age, and Tonnis grade is critical.',
    'title': 'Adult Hip Dysplasia PAO Outcomes',
